noun.name: bicycle
noun.discription: a two-wheeled vehicle powered by human pedaling

object1.name: motorcycle
object1.discription: in parallel with 'bicycle', is a two-wheeled vehicle powered by an internal combustion engine

object2.name: scooter
object2.discription: in parallel with 'bicycle', is a small, motorized or non-motorized vehicle with a platform for the feet

object3.name: tricycle
object3.discription: in parallel with 'bicycle', is a three-wheeled vehicle, often used by children or for cargo

object4.name: unicycle
object4.discription: in parallel with 'bicycle', is a one-wheeled vehicle, requiring balance and skill to ride

object5.name: skateboard
object5.discription: in parallel with 'bicycle', is a flat platform with wheels, ridden by standing and using feet to propel

object6.name: rollerblades
object6.discription: in parallel with 'bicycle', are inline skates that allow for fast movement on flat surfaces

object7.name: pogo stick
object7.discription: in parallel with 'bicycle', is a device for bouncing, consisting of a pole with a spring and foot platforms

object8.name: hoverboard
object8.discription: in parallel with 'bicycle', is a self-balancing, battery-powered scooter without pedals
